<p>POSIX.1 defines numerous constants that deals with implementation limits of os.</p>
<p>Â </p>
<p>1. Numerical limits: LONG_BIT, SSIZE_MAX, and WORD_BIT</p>
<p>2. Minimum values: the 25 constants in Figure 2.8</p>
<p>3. Maximum value: _POSIX_CLOCKRES_MIN</p>
<p>4. Runtime increasable values: CHARCLASS_NAME_MAX, COLL_WEIGHTS_MAX, LINE_MAX, NGROUPS_MAX, and RE_DUP_MAX</p>
<p>5. Runtime invariant values, possibly indeterminate: the 17 constants in Figure 2.9 (plus an additional four constants introduced in Section 12.2 and three constants introduced in Section 14.5)</p>
<p>6. Other invariant values: NL_ARGMAX, NL_MSGMAX, NL_SETMAX, and NL_TEXTMAX</p>
<p>7. Pathname variable values: FILESIZEBITS, LINK_MAX, MAX_CANON, MAX_INPUT, NAME_MAX, PATH_MAX, PIPE_BUF, and SYMLINK_MAX</p>
